This paper proposes a novel attention-based model for automatic image captioning, which is a problem in computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses different ways of generating attention areas, which involves training neural networks, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the MSCOCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark in multimedia (MM) research.
